{
  "text": "and -2.1 kJ/mole, respectively [CITATION_1] . Based on the studies, we found that the length of anchor has to be adjusted by the free energy prediction. In contrast to the previous design strategies--mismatch self-dimer or hairpin [CITATION_2] and DNA/RNA chimera (32)--, this locking-to-unlocking system allows us to efficiently predict the secondary structures of probes and therefore it could alleviate the demanding functional analysis by trial and error, in the design of novel probes. Based on this study, we envision developing a com- puterized design program that suggests an optimized foldback anchor sequence for each specific miRNA. Ultimately, the aim would be to produce a full set of DNA/AgNCs probes covering most of miRNAs in human and plants [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
